tation book\">Bureaux (1895). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=2rgEAAAAYAAJ&amp;pg=PA211\"><i>Le Photo-journal</i></a>. Bureaux.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Le+Photo-journal&amp;rft.pub=Bureaux&amp;rft.date=1895&amp;rft.au=Bureaux&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D2rgEAAAAYAAJ%26pg%3DPA211&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALightning+rod+fashion\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite id=\"CITEREFCamenzind2007\" class=\"citation book\">Camenzind, Hans (1 February 2007). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=VCUMQMTWCtMC&amp;pg=PA22\"><i>Much Ado about Almost Nothing</i></a>. Hans Camenzind. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-615-13995-1\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0-615-13995-1\">978-0-615-13995-1</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Much+Ado+about+Almost+Nothing&amp;rft.pub=Hans+Camenzind&amp;rft.date=2007-02-01&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-615-13995-1&amp;rft.aulast=Camenzind&amp;rft.aufirst=Hans&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DVCUMQMTWCtMC%26pg%3DPA22&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALightning+rod+fashion\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite id=\"CITEREFClairvilleCordier1851\" class=\"citation book\">Clairville; Cordier, Jules (1851). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=yblbAAAAQAAJ&amp;pg=PA31\"><i>Le Palais de Cristal ou les Parisiens \u00e0 Londres</i></a>. Beck. p.&#160;31.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Le+Palais+de+Cristal+ou+les+Parisiens+%C3%A0+Londres&amp;rft.pages=31&amp;rft.pub=Beck&amp;rft.date=1851&amp;rft.au=Clairville&amp;rft.au=Cordier%2C+Jules&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DyblbAAAAQAAJ%26pg%3DPA31&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALightning+rod+fashion\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite id=\"CITEREFDray2005\" class=\"citation book\">Dray, Philip (2 August 2005). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=Hjw4TwsfeqgC&amp;pg=PT148\"><i>Stealing God's Thunder</i></a>. <a href=\"/wiki/Random_House_Publishing_Group\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Random House Publishing Group\">Random House Publishing Group</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1-58836-461-6\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-1-58836-461-6\">978-1-58836-461-6</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Stealing+God%27s+Thunder&amp;rft.pub=Random+House+Publishing+Group&amp;rft.date=2005-08-02&amp;rft.isbn=978-1-58836-461-6&amp;rft.aulast=Dray&amp;rft.aufirst=Philip&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DHjw4TwsfeqgC%26pg%3DPT148&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALightning+rod+fashion\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite id=\"CITEREFFiguier1867\" class=\"citation book\">Figuier, Louis (1867). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=8DUVAAAAQAAJ&amp;pg=PA569\"><i>The wonders of science or popular description of modern inventions</i></a>. Furne, Juvet.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+wonders+of+science+or+popular+description+of+modern+inventions&amp;rft.pub=Furne%2C+Juvet&amp;rft.date=1867&amp;rft.aulast=Figuier&amp;rft.aufirst=Louis&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D8DUVAAAAQAAJ%26pg%3DPA569&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALightning+rod+fashion\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite id=\"CITEREFO&#39;Reilly2011\" class=\"citation book\">O'Reilly, James (27 December 2011). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=IwkVHLge2I4C&amp;pg=PA184\"><i>Travelers' Tales Paris</i></a>. Travelers' Tales. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1-60952-074-8\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-1-60952-074-8\">978-1-60952-074-8</a>. <q>Benjamin Franklin's discovery of atmospheric electricity did not give birth to a new French hairdress, but he was honored with a hat,\u201cle chapeau paratonnerre,\u201d with a little metal chain to attract lightning extending from the back of the hatband.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Travelers%27+Tales+Paris&amp;rft.pub=Travelers%27+Tales&amp;rft.date=2011-12-27&amp;rft.isbn=978-1-60952-074-8&amp;rft.aulast=O%27Reilly&amp;rft.aufirst=James&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DIwkVHLge2I4C%26pg%3DPA184&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALightning+rod+fashion\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite id=\"CITEREFSchiffer2003\" class=\"citation book\">Schiffer, Michael Brian (14 October 2003). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=xS9jvWe26OoC&amp;pg=PA190\"><i>Draw the Lightning Down</i></a>. <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_California_Press\" title=\"University of California Press\">University of California Press</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-520-23802-2\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0-520-23802-2\">978-0-520-23802-2</a>. <q>Public discussions of lightning conductors in France also took a more whimsical turn. If buildings could be protected from lightning, then why not people as well? In 1778 it was proposed that hats be equipped with lightning conductors. From a metal ring around the hat, a chain would dangle downward dragging on the ground behind the wearer of this most fashionable contrivance of millinery artistry.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Draw+the+Lightning+Down&amp;rft.pub=University+of+California+Press&amp;rft.date=2003-10-14&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-520-23802-2&amp;rft.aulast=Schiffer&amp;rft.aufirst=Michael+Brian&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DxS9jvWe26OoC%26pg%3DPA190&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALightning+rod+fashion\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite id=\"CITEREFSoci\u00e9t\u00e9_fran\u00e7aise_des_\u00e9lectriciens1936\" class=\"citation book\">Soci\u00e9t\u00e9 fran\u00e7aise des \u00e9lectriciens (1936). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=y5AoAQAAMAAJ\"><i>Bulletin</i></a>. <q>En 1778, on voit appara\u00eetre \u00e0 Paris la mode du chapeau paratonnerre pour les femmes; .. = In 1778, the fashion of the lightning rod hat for women appeared in Paris...</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Bulletin&amp;rft.date=1936&amp;rft.au=Soci%C3%A9t%C3%A9+fran%C3%A7aise+des+%C3%A9lectriciens&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3Dy5AoAQAAMAAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALightning+rod+fashion\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite id=\"CITEREFWilson1960\" class=\"citation book\">Wilson, Mitchell A. (1960). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=wcxEAAAAIAAJ\"><i>American Science and Invention, a Pictorial History: The Fabulous Story of how American Dreamers, Wizards, and Inspired Tinkerers Converted a Wilderness Into the Wonder of the World</i></a>. Bonanza Books.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=American+Science+and+Invention%2C+a+Pictorial+History%3A+The+Fabulous+Story+of+how+American+Dreamers%2C+Wizards%2C+and+Inspired+Tinkerers+Converted+a+Wilderness+Into+the+Wonder+of+the+World&amp;rft.pub=Bonanza+Books&amp;rft.date=1960&amp;rft.aulast=Wilson&amp;rft.aufirst=Mitchell+A.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DwcxEAAAAIAAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALightning+rod+fashion\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1238\nCached time: 20180908052336\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.180 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.215 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 660/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 21186/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 117/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 9637/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.096/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 3.12 MB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  172.282      1 -total\n 45.35%   78.130      1 Template:Reflist\n 26.94%   46.420      3 Template:Cite_news\n 26.51%   45.677     14 Template:Sfn\n 25.91%   44.635      9 Template:C